Extracted Variables:
- net: number of acres to use the net
- fishing_line: number of acres to use the fishing line
- sum_in_a: sum of acres in the lake
- linear_available: available units of bait
- linear_at_most: maximum units of pain the fisherman can tolerate

Definitions:
- net (n): n \geq 0, n \in \mathbb{Z}
- fishing_line (f): f \geq 0, f \in \mathbb{Z}
- sum_in_a (S): S = 250
- linear_available (A): A = 800
- linear_at_most (P): P = 350

Objective:
- Maximize the total number of fish caught by the fisherman

Constraints:
1. 8n + 5f \leq \text{max_fish}
2. 4n + 3f \leq A
3. 2n + f \leq P

Note: The comparison operators have been replaced with \leq for modeling purposes.
